"; Comprehensive Snapshot Mill — snapshot-comprehensive
; 4-AXIS (A-ROTARY) G-CODE — Siemens Sinumerik dialect
; ---------------------------------------------------------------------------
; UNVERIFIED G-CODE — verify every line against your Sinumerik controller
; documentation and machine data (MD) before running on a machine.
; Output is not guaranteed safe for any real machine.
; ---------------------------------------------------------------------------
; CRITICAL 4TH AXIS CHECKS BEFORE RUNNING:
; (1) Confirm the rotary table or chuck is firmly clamped to the machine table
;     and the A-axis servo is enabled in machine data.
; (2) Confirm the workpiece is centred on the rotary axis — off-centre
;     stock causes gouging and crashes.
; (3) Confirm cylinder diameter matches the value used to generate toolpaths.
; (4) Set A-axis WCS zero — touch off the A axis at your reference position.
;     Use Sinumerik HMI Work Offset screen to set the A zero.
; (5) Air-cut with spindle off at 10% feed override before a real cut.
; (6) Confirm your Sinumerik machine data has the A-axis properly configured:
;     MD30300 (IS_ROT_AX), MD30310 (ROT_IS_MODULO), MD36100 (POS_LIMIT_PLUS),
;     MD36110 (POS_LIMIT_MINUS) must match your rotary table capabilities.
; (7) Confirm jog, MDI, and reference modes work for the A axis before running
;     this program in AUTO mode.
; ---------------------------------------------------------------------------
; Retract order: lift Z to safe clearance before commanding large A moves.
; Before production: dry run — spindle off, Z high, feed reduced.
; See docs/MACHINES.MD — safe Z, WCS, units, spindle M-codes.
; ---------------------------------------------------------------------------
; Work area (mm): 300 x 200 x 100
; A-axis range: 360 deg — verify against Sinumerik MD soft limits
; --- Safety header ---
G21              ; millimeters — must match Sinumerik setting data SD42010
G90                    ; absolute distance mode (X Y Z A all absolute)
G17                    ; XY plane for G2/G3 arcs
G40                    ; cancel cutter radius compensation
G49                    ; cancel tool length compensation
G80                    ; cancel canned cycles
; Active work offset — verify fixture zero matches G54-G59 selection
G56
; Operation: Comprehensive Dialect Test
; --- Tool call (Sinumerik — verify tool number and D correction in tool table) ---
T2 D1                  ; select tool 2, cutting edge 1
M6                     ; execute tool change
; Home / safe position — retract Z before rotating A to avoid collisions
G0 Z100   ; safe Z retract — adjust to your actual safe clearance
; Spindle on (Sinumerik — confirm S value matches your spindle and tool)
M3 S9000
; --- 4-axis toolpath moves begin (X Y Z A words) ---
G0 X0 Y0 Z20 A0
G1 X10 Z-2.000 A0 F600
G1 X10 Z-2.000 A90 F400
G1 X10 Z-2.000 A180 F400
G1 X10 Z-2.000 A270 F400
G0 Z20 A0
; --- end toolpath ---
; Spindle off
M5
; Safe retract and park
G0 Z100   ; full retract for unload
G0 A0                  ; return A-axis to zero
G0 X0 Y0              ; park X Y — adjust to your preferred park position
M30                    ; program end and rewind
"
`;

exports[`Snapshot — every dialect with tool change and WCS > Siemens 5-axis with tool T2, WCS G56, RPM 9000 1`] = `
"; Comprehensive Snapshot Mill — snapshot-comprehensive
; 5-AXIS SIMULTANEOUS G-CODE — Siemens Sinumerik dialect
; ---------------------------------------------------------------------------
; UNVERIFIED G-CODE — verify every line against your controller manual before
; running on a machine. Output is not guaranteed safe for any real machine.
; ---------------------------------------------------------------------------
; CRITICAL 5-AXIS CHECKS BEFORE RUNNING:
; (1) Confirm machine data (MD) for kinematic chain matches this profile.
;     TRAORI reads pivot point distances from MD — wrong MD = wrong TCP.
; (2) Confirm TRAORI is licensed and configured ($MC_TRAFO_TYPE_1, etc.).
; (3) Confirm A-axis and B/C-axis travel limits and soft limits.
; (4) Confirm tool length in the tool table (D1) is correct.
; (5) Air-cut with spindle off at 10% feed override before any real cut.
; (6) CYCLE800 (SWIVEL) may be needed before TRAORI if using tilted work
;     planes — this template does not emit CYCLE800.
; ---------------------------------------------------------------------------
; Work area (mm): 300 x 200 x 100
; A-axis range: 360°
; B-axis range: 120°
; Kinematic chain: table-table
; Max tilt from vertical: 60°
G21        ; G21=mm / G20=inch — must match controller defaults
G90              ; absolute distance mode
G17              ; XY plane for arcs
; Active work offset — verify fixture zero matches G54–G59 selection
G56
; Operation: Comprehensive Dialect Test
; --- Activate 5-axis orientation transformation ---
; TRAORI tells Sinumerik to maintain tool tip at programmed XYZ regardless
; of rotary axis positions. This is mandatory for simultaneous 5-axis.
TRAORI(1)        ; activate transformation — number matches your kinematic setup
; Spindle on
M3 S9000
; --- 5-axis toolpath moves begin (X Y Z A B words) ---
G0 X0 Y0 Z30 A0 B0
G1 X10 Y10 Z-1.000 A15 B10 F500
G1 X20 Y10 Z-1.000 A30 B-5 F500
G1 X20 Y20 Z-1.500 A15 B0 F500
G0 Z30 A0 B0
; --- end toolpath ---
; Spindle off
M5
; Deactivate transformation before retracting
TRAFOOF          ; transformation off
; Safe retract
G0 Z100
G0 A0 B0         ; return rotary axes to zero
G0 X0 Y0         ; park — adjust to your safe park position
M30
"
`;

exports[`Snapshot — inverse time feed mode > inverse time feed DISABLED: no G93/G94 in output 1`] = `
"; Comprehensive Snapshot Mill — snapshot-comprehensive
; 4-AXIS (A-ROTARY) G-CODE — grbl_4axis dialect
; ---------------------------------------------------------------------------
; UNVERIFIED G-CODE — verify every line against your Carvera firmware docs
; and your rotary attachment manual before running on the machine.
; ---------------------------------------------------------------------------
; CRITICAL 4TH AXIS CHECKS BEFORE RUNNING:
; (1) Confirm the rotary attachment is firmly clamped to the table.
; (2) Confirm the workpiece is centred on the rotary chuck — off-centre
;     stock causes gouging and crashes.
; (3) Confirm cylinder diameter matches the value used to generate toolpaths.
; (4) Set A-axis WCS zero (usually the left face of the cylinder, A=0°).
; (5) Air-cut with spindle off at 10 % feed override before a real cut.
; (6) Confirm your Carvera firmware supports the A word in Grbl (some builds
;     require the rotary axis plugin — check Makera documentation).
; ---------------------------------------------------------------------------
; Retract order: lift Z to a safe radial clearance before commanding large A moves
; (toolpath lines already use clearance Z between passes; header retract is machine max Z).
; Before production: dry run — spindle off, Z high, feed reduced.
; Compare a short program to a known-good file from Makera CAM.
; See docs/MACHINES.md — safe Z, WCS, units, spindle M-codes.
; ---------------------------------------------------------------------------
; Work area (mm): 300 x 200 x 100
; A-axis range: ±360° (verify against firmware soft limits)
G21              ; millimeters — must match Carvera controller settings
G90              ; absolute distance mode (X Y Z A all absolute)
G17              ; XY plane for G2/G3 arcs; 4-axis arcs use XZ with G18 if needed
; Operation: No Inverse Time
; Home / safe position — retract Z before rotating A to avoid collisions
G0 Z100 ; safe Z retract — adjust to your actual safe clearance
G0 Y0            ; CRITICAL: center tool on rotation axis (Y must be 0 for 4-axis rotary)
; Spindle on (Grbl — confirm S value matches your bit and material)
M3 S12000
; --- 4-axis toolpath moves begin (X Y Z A words) ---
G0 X0 Y0 Z20 A0
G1 X10 Z-2.000 A0 F600
G1 X10 Z-2.000 A90 F400
G1 X10 Z-2.000 A180 F400
G1 X10 Z-2.000 A270 F400
G0 Z20 A0
; --- end toolpath ---
; Spindle off
M5
; Retract Z to machine max clearance and park
; (Toolpath already returns A to 0° and retracts Z to clearance;
;  this final retract ensures the tool is at machine-max Z for unload.)
G0 Z100 ; full retract for unload
G0 X0 Y0        ; park X, re-center Y on rotation axis
; M30 or M2 if your Grbl build supports program end (comment out if unsupported)
M30
"
`;

exports[`Snapshot — inverse time feed mode > inverse time feed ENABLED: G93 before toolpath, G94 after 1`] = `
"; Comprehensive Snapshot Mill — snapshot-comprehensive
; 4-AXIS (A-ROTARY) G-CODE — grbl_4axis dialect
; ---------------------------------------------------------------------------
; UNVERIFIED G-CODE — verify every line against your Carvera firmware docs
; and your rotary attachment manual before running on the machine.
; ---------------------------------------------------------------------------
; CRITICAL 4TH AXIS CHECKS BEFORE RUNNING:
; (1) Confirm the rotary attachment is firmly clamped to the table.
; (2) Confirm the workpiece is centred on the rotary chuck — off-centre
;     stock causes gouging and crashes.
; (3) Confirm cylinder diameter matches the value used to generate toolpaths.
; (4) Set A-axis WCS zero (usually the left face of the cylinder, A=0°).
; (5) Air-cut with spindle off at 10 % feed override before a real cut.
; (6) Confirm your Carvera firmware supports the A word in Grbl (some builds
;     require the rotary axis plugin — check Makera documentation).
; ---------------------------------------------------------------------------
; Retract order: lift Z to a safe radial clearance before commanding large A moves
; (toolpath lines already use clearance Z between passes; header retract is machine max Z).
; Before production: dry run — spindle off, Z high, feed reduced.
; Compare a short program to a known-good file from Makera CAM.
; See docs/MACHINES.md — safe Z, WCS, units, spindle M-codes.
; ---------------------------------------------------------------------------
; Work area (mm): 300 x 200 x 100
; A-axis range: ±360° (verify against firmware soft limits)
G21              ; millimeters — must match Carvera controller settings
G90              ; absolute distance mode (X Y Z A all absolute)
G17              ; XY plane for G2/G3 arcs; 4-axis arcs use XZ with G18 if needed
; Operation: Inverse Time Enabled
; Home / safe position — retract Z before rotating A to avoid collisions
G0 Z100 ; safe Z retract — adjust to your actual safe clearance
G0 Y0            ; CRITICAL: center tool on rotation axis (Y must be 0 for 4-axis rotary)
; Spindle on (Grbl — confirm S value matches your bit and material)
M3 S12000
; --- Inverse-time feed mode (G93) for continuous rotary axis motion ---
; F-word = 1/time (inverse minutes). Each G1 block must carry its own F value.
; G94 is restored after the toolpath to return to normal feed-per-minute mode.
; NOTE: Not all Grbl builds support G93. Verify your firmware supports it.
G93              ; inverse-time feed mode ON
; --- 4-axis toolpath moves begin (X Y Z A words) ---
G0 X0 Y0 Z20 A0
G1 X10 Z-2.000 A0 F600
G1 X10 Z-2.000 A90 F400
G1 X10 Z-2.000 A180 F400
G1 X10 Z-2.000 A270 F400
G0 Z20 A0
; --- end toolpath ---
G94              ; restore feed-per-minute mode
; Spindle off
M5
; Retract Z to machine max clearance and park
; (Toolpath already returns A to 0° and retracts Z to clearance;
;  this final retract ensures the tool is at machine-max Z for unload.)
G0 Z100 ; full retract for unload
G0 X0 Y0        ; park X, re-center Y on rotation axis
; M30 or M2 if your Grbl build supports program end (comment out if unsupported)
M30
"
`;

exports[`Snapshot — inverse time feed mode > inverse time feed on Carvera 4-axis 1`] = `
"; Makera Carvera — 4-Axis Rotary G-code
; Machine: Carvera Snapshot — carvera-snapshot
; Operation: Carvera Inverse Time
; ---------------------------------------------------------------------------
; SAFETY CHECKLIST:
; [1] Rotary attachment secured to table
; [2] Stock centered in chuck, tailstock engaged
; [3] Stock diameter matches CAM setup (Y dimension)
; [4] Z=0 is at stock CENTER (rotation axis), NOT surface
; [5] A=0 set via controller or G28.3 A0
; [6] Air-cut first: spindle off, Z raised, 10% feed override
; ---------------------------------------------------------------------------
; UNVERIFIED G-CODE — verify every line against your Carvera firmware docs
; and your rotary attachment manual before running on the machine.
; Before production: dry run — spindle off, Z high, feed reduced.
; Compare a short program to a known-good file from Makera CAM.
; See docs/MACHINES.md — safe Z, WCS, units, spindle M-codes.
; ---------------------------------------------------------------------------
; Work area (mm): 300 x 200 x 100
; A-axis range: continuous (verify against firmware soft limits)
; Spindle range: 6000–15000 RPM
; ---------------------------------------------------------------------------
G21              ; millimeters
G90              ; absolute positioning
G17              ; XY plane
; Safe retract, center on rotary axis, and spindle start
G0 Z100 ; safe Z retract
G0 Y0            ; CRITICAL: center tool on rotation axis (Y must be 0 for 4-axis)
M3 S12000
G4 P2            ; dwell 2s for spindle to reach speed
; --- Inverse-time feed mode (G93) for continuous rotary axis motion ---
G93              ; inverse-time feed mode ON
; --- 4-axis toolpath moves begin (X Y Z A words) ---
G0 X0 Y0 Z20 A0
G1 X10 Z-2.000 A0 F600
G1 X10 Z-2.000 A90 F400
G1 X10 Z-2.000 A180 F400
G1 X10 Z-2.000 A270 F400
G0 Z20 A0
; --- end toolpath ---
G94              ; restore feed-per-minute mode
; --- End ---
M5
G0 Z100 ; retract Z
G0 A0            ; return A to zero
G0 X0 Y0        ; park X, re-center Y on rotation axis
M9               ; coolant/vacuum off
M2               ; program end (NOT M30 — M30 may delete file on Smoothieware)
"
`;

exports[`Snapshot — inverse time feed mode > inverse time feed on Fanuc 4-axis 1`] = `
"(Comprehensive Snapshot Mill — snapshot-comprehensive)
(4-AXIS A-ROTARY G-CODE — FANUC DIALECT)
(---------------------------------------------------------------------------)
(UNVERIFIED G-CODE — VERIFY EVERY LINE AGAINST YOUR FANUC CONTROLLER MANUAL)
(BEFORE RUNNING ON A MACHINE. OUTPUT IS NOT GUARANTEED SAFE FOR ANY MACHINE.)
(---------------------------------------------------------------------------)
(CRITICAL 4TH AXIS CHECKS BEFORE RUNNING:)
(1 — CONFIRM THE ROTARY TABLE OR CHUCK IS FIRMLY CLAMPED TO THE MACHINE TABLE.)
(2 — CONFIRM THE WORKPIECE IS CENTRED ON THE ROTARY AXIS — OFF-CENTRE)
(    STOCK CAUSES GOUGING AND CRASHES.)
(3 — CONFIRM CYLINDER DIAMETER MATCHES THE VALUE USED TO GENERATE TOOLPATHS.)
(4 — SET A-AXIS WCS ZERO — USUALLY THE LEFT FACE OF THE CYLINDER AT A=0 DEG.)
(5 — AIR-CUT WITH SPINDLE OFF AT 10 PCT FEED OVERRIDE BEFORE A REAL CUT.)
(6 — CONFIRM YOUR FANUC CONTROL SUPPORTS A-AXIS COMMANDS AND THAT THE)
(    ROTARY AXIS IS PROPERLY CONFIGURED IN PARAMETERS.)
(---------------------------------------------------------------------------)
(RETRACT ORDER: LIFT Z TO SAFE CLEARANCE BEFORE COMMANDING LARGE A MOVES.)
(BEFORE PRODUCTION: DRY RUN — SPINDLE OFF, Z HIGH, FEED REDUCED.)
(SEE DOCS/MACHINES.MD — SAFE Z, WCS, UNITS, SPINDLE M-CODES.)
(---------------------------------------------------------------------------)
(WORK AREA MM: 300 X 200 X 100)
(A-AXIS RANGE: 360 DEG — VERIFY AGAINST MACHINE TRAVEL LIMITS)
G21              (METRIC — MUST MATCH CONTROLLER SETTING)
G90                    (ABSOLUTE DISTANCE MODE — X Y Z A ALL ABSOLUTE)
G17                    (XY PLANE FOR G2/G3 ARCS)
G40 G49 G80           (CANCEL CUTTER COMP, TOOL LENGTH COMP, CANNED CYCLES)
(OPERATION: Fanuc Inverse Time)
(SAFE RETRACT — LIFT Z BEFORE ANY A-AXIS ROTATION TO AVOID COLLISIONS)
G0 Z100
(SPINDLE ON — CONFIRM S VALUE MATCHES YOUR TOOL AND MATERIAL)
M3 S10000
(--- INVERSE-TIME FEED MODE G93 FOR CONTINUOUS ROTARY AXIS MOTION ---)
(F-WORD = 1/TIME — INVERSE MINUTES. EACH G1 BLOCK MUST CARRY ITS OWN F VALUE.)
(G94 IS RESTORED AFTER THE TOOLPATH TO RETURN TO NORMAL FEED-PER-MINUTE MODE.)
G93                    (INVERSE-TIME FEED MODE ON)
(--- 4-AXIS TOOLPATH MOVES BEGIN — X Y Z A WORDS ---)
G0 X0 Y0 Z20 A0
G1 X10 Z-2.000 A0 F600
G1 X10 Z-2.000 A90 F400
G1 X10 Z-2.000 A180 F400
G1 X10 Z-2.000 A270 F400
G0 Z20 A0
(--- END TOOLPATH ---)
G94                    (RESTORE FEED-PER-MINUTE MODE)
(SPINDLE OFF)
M5
(SAFE RETRACT AND RETURN TO REFERENCE POSITION)
G91 G28 Z0            (RETURN Z TO REFERENCE POINT — INCREMENTAL MODE)
G91 G28 X0 Y0         (RETURN X Y TO HOME POSITION)
G90                    (RESTORE ABSOLUTE MODE)
G0 A0                 (RETURN A-AXIS TO ZERO)
M30                   (PROGRAM END AND REWIND)
"
`;

